  "description": "Levels configuration for Colour Sort. Each level is a self-contained sorting puzzle. The game engine presents items and bins — the child drags items to the correct bin. No questions are asked; mastery is demonstrated by completing the sort correctly. Levels progress from single-attribute sorts (band 1) through two-attribute Venn and Carroll diagrams (band 2).",
  "progression_rules": {
    "warm_up_from_previous_band": true,
    "warm_up_percentage": 0.25,
    "mastery_threshold": 0.85,
    "mastery_window": 8,
    "unlock_on_mastery": true,
    "note": "Levels unlock sequentially within a tier. A child must complete a level with 85% accuracy across 8 attempts before the next level unlocks. Band 1 sorts by a single visible attribute. Band 2 introduces two attributes and overlap (Venn) and grid (Carroll) layouts."
  },
